"Most application kernels live entirely in Tier 1 or straddle Tier 1 and 2. "
"Tier 3 is for performance engineers building at the level of CUTLASS or "
"Triton IR. If you are writing a vecadd, a GEMM, or a reduction, you will "
"rarely leave Tier 2."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu-safety/the-safety-model.md:40
msgid "Tier 1: safe by default"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu-safety/the-safety-model.md:42
msgid "The core idea: `DisjointSlice<T>` + `ThreadIndex`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu-safety/the-safety-model.md:44
msgid ""
"The primary device-side safety abstraction is a pair of types that together "
"support race-free parallel writes:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu-safety/the-safety-model.md:47
msgid ""
"**`ThreadIndex<'kernel, IndexSpace>`** -- an opaque witness around a "
"`usize`, with no public constructor. The only way to obtain one is through "
"trusted functions (`index_1d`, `index_2d::<S>`) that derive the value from "
"**hardware built-in variables** (`threadIdx`, `blockIdx`, `blockDim`) -- "
"read-only special registers the runtime fills in at launch. `ThreadIndex` is "
"`!Send + !Sync + !Copy + !Clone`, and the `'kernel` lifetime ties it to a "
"stack-local scope inside the kernel body, so it cannot be smuggled across "
"threads via shared memory or outlive the kernel."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu-safety/the-safety-model.md:56
msgid ""
"**`DisjointSlice<T, IndexSpace>`** -- a slice-like type whose `get_mut()` "
"method only accepts a `ThreadIndex` whose `IndexSpace` matches its own. "
"Returns `Option<&mut T>` -- `None` for out-of-bounds indices."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu-safety/the-safety-model.md:61
msgid "Put them together and you get a kernel body with zero `unsafe`:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu-safety/the-safety-model.md:63
msgid ""
"use cuda_device::{kernel, DisjointSlice};\n"
"\n"
"#[kernel]\n"
"pub fn vecadd(a: &[f32], b: &[f32], mut c: DisjointSlice<f32>) {\n"
"    if let Some((c_elem, idx)) = c.get_mut_indexed() {\n"
"        let i = idx.get();\n"
"        *c_elem = a[i] + b[i];\n"
"    }\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu-safety/the-safety-model.md:75
msgid ""
"`get_mut_indexed` is the one-call form: it mints the per-thread witness and "
"resolves it to a `&mut T` in a single shot. The explicit two-step form is "
"also available when you need the index for parallel arithmetic on multiple "
"slices:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu-safety/the-safety-model.md:80
msgid ""
"#[kernel]\n"
"pub fn vecadd(a: &[f32], b: &[f32], mut c: DisjointSlice<f32>) {\n"
"    let idx = thread::index_1d();\n"
"    if let Some(c_elem) = c.get_mut(idx) {\n"
"        let i = idx.get();\n"
"        *c_elem = a[i] + b[i];\n"
"    }\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu-safety/the-safety-model.md:91
msgid "Safety follows from five facts:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu-safety/the-safety-model.md:93
msgid ""
"`index_1d()` uses only X coordinates. Its value is unique when block and "
"grid Y/Z dimensions are all 1. A `domain = 1` prepared launch proves that; a "
"raw launch must prove it in its `unsafe` block."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu-safety/the-safety-model.md:96
msgid "`get_mut()` is bounds-checked -- out-of-range threads get `None`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu-safety/the-safety-model.md:97
msgid ""
"The `IndexSpace` parameter ties each witness to its layout: a "
"`DisjointSlice<T, Index2D<128>>` will not accept a `ThreadIndex<'_, "
"Index2D<256>>` -- mixing strides is a compile error."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu-safety/the-safety-model.md:100
msgid ""
"The witness is `!Send + !Sync + !Copy + !Clone` and `'kernel`-scoped, so "
"threads cannot launder each other's indices through shared memory."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu-safety/the-safety-model.md:102
msgid ""
"A checked `PreparedLaunch<K>` ties the host geometry to the exact kernel."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu-safety/the-safety-model.md:104
msgid ""
"The borrow checker sees a single `&mut T` per thread. The hardware provides "
"the coordinates; the launch proof makes their linearization disjoint. The "
"type system ties the device and host proofs together."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu-safety/the-safety-model.md:108
msgid ""
"1D prepared launch: Y=Z=1 -> index_1d values are unique -> safe get_mut\n"
"raw 2D launch:       grid/block Y > 1 repeats X indices -> caller-unsafe\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu-safety/the-safety-model.md:113
msgid "Trusted index functions"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu-safety/the-safety-model.md:115
msgid ""
"`ThreadIndex` is only as trustworthy as the functions that create it. Here "
"are the constructors cuda-oxide provides:"
